===Personnel===
*[[Bob Dylan]]&nbsp;<U+2013> [[acoustic guitar|acoustic]] [[guitar]], [[piano]], [[Singing|vocals]]
*[[Rick Danko]]&nbsp;<U+2013> [[bass guitar]], [[mandolin]], vocals
*[[Levon Helm]]&nbsp;<U+2013> [[Drum kit|drums]], [[mandolin]], bass guitar, vocals
*[[Garth Hudson]]&nbsp;<U+2013> [[Organ (music)|organ]], [[clavinet]], [[accordion]], [[tenor saxophone|tenor]]  [[saxophone]], piano
*[[Richard Manuel]]&nbsp;<U+2013> piano, drums, [[harmonica]], vocals
*[[Robbie Robertson]]&nbsp;<U+2013> [[electric guitar]], acoustic guitar, drums, vocals<ref name=marcus1975>{{harvnb|Marcus|1975}}</ref>

===Cover art===
The cover photograph for the 1975 album was taken by designer and photographer [[Reid Miles]] in the basement of a Los Angeles [[YMCA]]. It poses Dylan and the Band alongside characters suggested by the songs: a woman in a Mrs. Henry T-shirt, an Eskimo, a circus strongman and a dwarf  who has been identified as [[Angelo Rossitto]].<ref name=linderman>{{cite web|last=Linderman|first=Jim|title=The Basement Tapes Reid Miles Bob Dylan Genuine Photo Outtake Photo Shoot by Jim Linderman|url=http://chalktalkbooks.blogspot.com/2011/04/basement-tapes-reid-miles-bob-dylan.html|work=Essays On Bob Dylan By Jim Linderman|accessdate=7 January 2013}}</ref> Robertson wears a blue [[Mao suit|Mao-style suit]],and Manuel wears a [[U.S. Air Force]] uniform.<ref>{{harvnb|Hoskyns|1993|p=313}}</ref> [[Michael Gray (author)|Michael Gray]] has identified musicians [[David Blue (musician)|David Blue]] and [[Neil Young]] in the photo.<ref>{{harvnb|Gray|2006|p=38}}</ref> Others have claimed that Young was not in the photo.<ref name=linderman/>

===Reception and sales===
{{Album reviews
| title = Professional ratings
| rev1 = [[Allmusic]]
